  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Requirement binding references the ASTM F1841-97 hemolysis testing standard as the normative acceptance baseline; the bound model baseline reflects a 2026-Q1 product revision incorporating updated impeller geometry derived from post-2023 design changes. No update mechanism or gap analysis is documented between the 1997 standard and current product configuration.",
